<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>CSS Selectors Practice Page</title>

  <style>
    /* ====== General Page Styling ====== */
    body {
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Arial, sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      background-color: #f5f6f8;
      color: #333;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    header, footer {
      background-color: #2c3e50;
      color: white;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
    }

    main {
      padding: 2rem;
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: auto;
      background-color: white;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    }

    section {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    h2 {
      color: #2980b9;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #eee;
      padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    /* ====== ELEMENT SELECTOR ====== */
    /* Applies style to all paragraph elements */
    p {
      color: #444;
      padding-left: 10px;
    }

    /* ====== CLASS SELECTOR ====== */
    /* Styles all elements with the class "highlight" */
    .highlight {
      background-color: #fef4c5;
      border-left: 4px solid #f1c40f;
      padding: 0.5rem;
    }

    /* ====== ID SELECTOR ====== */
    /* Targets a specific element with id "special-text" */
    #special-text {
      color: #e74c3c;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    /* ====== ATTRIBUTE SELECTOR ====== */
    /* Targets links that open in a new tab */
    a[target="_blank"] {
      color: #27ae60;
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    /* ====== COMBINATORS ====== */
    /* Child Selector (>) – only direct child paragraphs of section */
    section > p {
      font-style: italic;
    }

    /* Adjacent Sibling (+) – first paragraph immediately after an h3 */
    h3 + p {
      color: #8e44ad;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    /* General Sibling (~) – all paragraphs after a list */
    ul ~ p {
      background-color: #dfe6e9;
      padding: 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 5px;
    }

    /* Descendant Selector – selects all <li> inside <ul> */
    ul li {
      color: #2c3e50;
    }

    /* ====== Layout Adjustments ====== */
    ul {
      padding-left: 2rem;
    }

    footer {
      margin-top: 2rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <header>
    <h1>CSS Selectors Practice Page</h1>
    <p>Demonstrating element, class, ID, attribute, and combinator selectors.</p>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section>
      <h2>1. Element Selector</h2>
      <p>This is a regular paragraph styled using the <strong>element selector</strong>.</p>
      <p>All paragraph elements on this page share this style.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Class Selector</h2>
      <p class="highlight">This paragraph has a <code>.highlight</code> class to show how class selectors work.</p>
      <p class="highlight">You can reuse this class on multiple elements.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. ID Selector</h2>
      <p id="special-text">This paragraph has an ID selector <code>#special-text</code>.</p>
      <p>IDs are unique and applied to only one element per page.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Attribute Selector</h2>
      <p>Below are links using attribute selectors:</p>
      <a href="https://www.example.com" target="_blank">External Link (new tab)</a><br>
      <a href="https://www.local.com">Internal Link (same tab)</a>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. Combinators</h2>
      <h3>Child Selector (>)</h3>
      <p>This paragraph is a direct child of a section — styled italic using <code>section > p</code>.</p>

      <h3>Adjacent Sibling (+)</h3>
      <p>This paragraph comes right after an h3 — styled purple using <code>h3 + p</code>.</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Apples</li>
        <li>Bananas</li>
        <li>Cherries</li>
      </ul>

      <p>This paragraph comes after a list — styled with background using <code>ul ~ p</code>.</p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <p>Created by [Your Name] | CSS Selectors Practice</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
